  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of the investigators work was to evaluate the impact of 4 sequentially
      implemented measures for preventing VAP in a major heart surgery ICU. The measures were a
      specific training program, aspiration of subglottic secretions (ASS), introduction of an
      inclinometer to improve the semirecumbent position, and reinforcement of oral care with
      chlorhexidine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
